{"key":"processedPost-17588971","value":{"id":17588971,"first":17588789,"last":17588996,"when":1358861005,"utime":"01/22/13 03:23 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>listerine said:</strong><br />Sorry, I should be more clear. It is solid, in a petridish. Solid enough that it is stored upside down.<br />I plan on scraping a spore print onto it in a still air box.<br />Do you think i need to dry them? Or did something slip his mind?</blockquote><br />Never store dishes upside down.<br />Hospital agar is for determining what kind of bacteria is infecting people and is usually blood based-not suitable for mushrooms.<br />You don't 'dry' agar.<br />'scraping' a print onto agar is a good way to damage spores and transfer contaminants.&nbsp; Use an inoculating loop as shown in the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Agar-Petri-Dishes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">agar-petri dish tek</a>.<br />I prefer MEA for mushroom growing.<br />RR"}}